                   "id":491,
                   "title":"Some people prefer jobs with no requirement of hightech skills. However, I enjoy hightech jobs such as those in use of computer a lot. \nFirst, walking into almost any business, you'll quickly see how hightech has transformed the way we work. Whether you're an entrepreneur, a bike courier, or a criminal lawyer, one thing is clear: our lives are surrounded by hightech. There's no escape and the hightech makes our jobs more convenient. So just enjoy it. \nSecond, hightech has made us more responsive, more able to gain access to information over a broader spectrum, and more effective to deal with our work. For example, it has taken our information and, instead of putting it into little cubbyholes of the company, made it broadly accessible. It makes that information much more functional and dynamic.",
