                   {
                   "id":718,
                   "title":"   I prefer high tech jobs. First, actually my major is computer science, so doing a high tech job can make full use of my major knowledge and if I do the job that with no requirement of high tech skills, I may be not as well as others who majored in other majors. \n   Second, jobs in the high tech industry have a strong potential for growth, as you can see, everyone is using high tech product nowadays, in fact The high tech sector has become a major source of economic growth fueling the economy, the future is just brighter doing a high tech job than doing a job that not related to high tech skills.\n   These are the reasons why I chose to take a high tech job.",
                   "references":"[{\"content\":\"DIVERSITY IN HIGH TECH\",\"link\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.eeoc.gov\u002Feeoc\u002Fstatistics\u002Freports\u002Fhightech\u002F\"}]",
                   "audio_url":"http:\u002F\u002Ftftsandbox.oss-cn-shanghai.aliyuncs.com\u002Fpolly_speeches\u002Fanswer-718.mp3",
                   "updatedAt":"2017-07-13T15:07:44.000Z",
